Title: Bay Area Rapid Transit
Description: The San Francisco Bay Area Rapid Transit District is a heavy-rail public transit system that connects the San Francisco Peninsula with communities in the East Bay and South Bay. BART operates in five counties with 131 miles of track and 50 stations, carrying approximately 405,000 trips on an average weekday.
